    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Double windows of Dutch origin; windows are divided in four sections, with the lower halves covered by shutters or doors and the upper halves glazed. A related design is seen in "kloosterkozijns," resembling one-half of the kruiskozijn.</Note_Text>
